helpful for Twitter that it was specifically negotiated.[4] Hmm. A =E2=80=
=9Cmisrepresentation=E2=80=9D? A quarter is like 90 days, so daily sampling=
 for 9,000 accounts per quarter would seem to be about 100 accounts per day=
. I can see his point here. Their point, though, is that he=E2=80=99s not s=
upposed to disclose what they tell him publicly, and he=E2=80=99s especiall=
y not supposed to brag about breaching his confidentiality agreement.[5] Ma=
ybe his plan all along was to pretend to buy Twitter, ruin its business and=
 run away? That seems pretty far-fetched, but on the other hand Musk keeps =
tweeting memes suggesting that it=E2=80=99s true? That this was all a galax=
y-brain plan to expose Twitter=E2=80=99s bot problem? Okay.
